    "congress": 119,
    "constitutionalAuthorityStatementText": "<pre>\n[Congressional Record Volume 171, Number 63 (Tuesday, April 8, 2025)]\n[House]\nFrom the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href=\"https://www.gpo.gov\">www.gpo.gov</a>]\nBy Mr. CRANE:\nH.R. 2705.\nCongress has the power to enact this legislation pursuant\nto the following:\nArticle I, Section 8, clause 3 provides Congress with the\npower to ``regulate commerce with foreign nations, and among\nthe several states, and with the Indian tribes.'' The Supreme\nCourt has held that Congress's power to regulate foreign\ncommerce includes the power to regulate the entry of persons\ninto the country. See Henderson v. Mayor of New York, 92 U.S.\n259, 270-71 (1876).\n[Page H1508]\n</pre>",
